Package <Unnamed>

  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    Book
    Book class defines the abstract data type Book, which is designed with a title (represented by name) a date published, a serial number, and variable to track if checked out.
    Commands
    Commands class contains info on what each console command means.
    Date
    Date class provides the structure for the Date object, which contains a year, month and day.
    IoFields
    IoFields class contains String messages that are used to display info about user commands that are handled by the Kiosk class
    Kiosk
    Kiosk class provides the interface for communicating with a Library object and handles input and output * by processing commands from the console.This includes dealing with additions/removal to a Library, printing a Library, * Checking out and returning books, etc.
    Library
    Library class is a container class that is designed to hold Book objects.
    RunProject1
    RunProject1 class is a simple driver class to display the functionality of Project 1
